subSubSection.paragraph:
Chthonius leoi
differs from
C. jonicus
in the following main characters: eyes absent (anterior eyes with flat lens, posterior eyes reduced to a pale cuticular area in
C. jonicus
); chelicerae with 1 or 2 lateral microsetae (without lateral microsetae in
C. jonicus
); chela length 0.38–0.40 mm ( 0.40–0.51 mm in
C. jonicus
); movable chelal finger length
0.225 –0.265 mm
( 0.275–0.34 mm in
C. jonicus
); movable chelal finger with coupled sensilla pc on a noticeable tubercle (coupled sensilla pc not on a tubercle in
C. jonicus
).
